Prayers for #damarhamlin🙏🏼

Via @apnews @tnd @local12wkrc: Monday night's Bengals game was suspended with 5:58 left in the first quarter after Bills safety Damar Hamlin required CPR after collapsing following a tackle. Medical personnel from both teams immediately rushed onto the field and were seen performing chest compressions on Hamlin. The CPR lasted approximately nine minutes before Hamlin was then placed in an ambulance and taken from the field. 

The NFL Players Association released a statement about the incident: “The NFLPA and everyone in our community is praying for Damar Hamlin. We have been in touch with Bills and Bengals players, and with the NFL. The only thing that matters at this moment is Damar’s health and well being. 

The NFL then released a statement that it agreed with the NFLPA to suspend the game. 

NFL: “Our thoughts are with Damar and the Buffalo Bills.” 

📸 @foxsanantonio

Hi everyone, some personal news to share:

After nearly 8 years, I have decided to leave FOX SA/ABC45. My last day on air is January 12. 

It has been a remarkable journey doing what I love every day in the beautiful city of San Antonio. From being out in the field reporting to launching my franchise SA STRONG, I have met incredible people from all walks of life. 

It has been an absolute privilege to share your stories. Thank you for trusting me. 

I’m incredibly grateful to management for believing in me and granting me this opportunity. A huge thank you to the entire FOX SA family, who works tirelessly every day to put on our newscasts. Thank you to my talented 9pm team, @ryanwolf9653 , @alexgarcia.tvwx , @yami_virgin , and @chuck.miketinac , for all the support and dedication. 

The community that I have built in this city reminds me every day of why I got into journalism. San Antonio, you have been my home away from home. Thank you for this monumental chapter. 💫🤍

-Camilla

My sweet Kaira👑 crossed the rainbow bridge on January 12th🌈 She found me at the start of my journey in San Antonio. 8 years of pure joy and love.🤍My best friend. My soul mate. My welcome home. She was there for relationships, heartbreaks, and everything in between. She fought so hard after being diagnosed with Chylothorax. My heart hurts - but it brings me peace knowing she is now free from the pain. Forever, my girl. Missing her every day. Rest easy, sweet angel. 🕊️Hold your pets extra tight. Time with them is never long enough.
